🧠 🛠️ Complete Troubleshooting Guide (Step-by-Step)
✅ Step 1: Check existing containers
docker ps -a

👉 Look for:

Same container name
Stopped containers
✅ Step 2: If name already exists
✔ Remove it completely:
docker rm -f web_server1

👉 This fixes:

“container name already in use” error
✅ Step 3: Check running containers (port usage)
docker ps

👉 Look for:

0.0.0.0:8080->80/tcp
✅ Step 4: If port already in use

👉 Change port:

docker run -d -p 8081:80 --name web_server1 nginx
✅ Step 5: Run container properly
docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name web_server1 nginx
✅ Step 6: Verify container is running
docker ps

👉 Status should be:

Up ...
✅ Step 7: Test in browser
http://localhost:8080

👉 If page loads → success ✅

🚨 If still error → advanced fixes
🔹 Clean stopped containers
docker container prune
🔹 Check logs (debugging)
docker logs web_server1
🔹 Restart Docker (rare cases)

👉 Sometimes Docker Desktop glitch happens

🎯 Golden Rules (VERY IMPORTANT)
🔥 Rule 1:

👉 Container name must be unique

🔥 Rule 2:

👉 Port must be free

🔥 Rule 3:

👉 Image must support the port (like nginx → 80)

🔥 Rule 4:

👉 Always follow syntax:

docker run [OPTIONS] IMAGE
🧠 Quick Memory Shortcut

👉 “Check → Remove → Run → Verify → Open”
